programme.title: First Ladies
programme.desc: Aired 10/4/2020. In 2008, Michelle Obama became the first African American first lady after her husband, Barack Obama, was elected as the first African American President of the United States. Michelle and Barack were elected on a wave of euphoria, but not everyone shared in the enthusiasm of the moment and they endured vicious attacks. In spite of this, Michelle’s popularity climbed, and she became a critical factor in President Obama’s re-election in 2012. During her time in the White House, Michelle used her platform to speak on issues such as gun violence and launched the Let’s Move! initiative dedicated to combating childhood obesity.

programme.title: First Ladies

programme.title: First Ladies

From Ronald Reagan’s first campaign for the White House in 1980, to his Cold War ending triumph in 1987, Nancy Reagan was pulling strings and calling the shots behind the scenes.

programme.title: First Ladies
programme.desc: Aired 10/25/2020. Eleanor Roosevelt’s marriage to Franklin Delano Roosevelt created arguably the most formidable political partnership in American history. programme.desc: We are in our home state of Ohio this week and we are hosting the owner of Black Widow Deer Lures, Andy and his wife Janice for an early season hunt on some of our farms. The weather was warm and the deer movement was slow but it was a great week spending time with Andy and Janice. Briar is my 11 year old son who has worked extremely hard this past year putting up Spartan Trail Cameras, helping with food plots and hanging tree stands. I have always wanted him to earn his hunts and especially the opportunities at a big buck. This year was his year. Because he worked so hard in the off season he earned his chance at a really good deer. Early November rolled around and he finally got his chance. He shot the biggest deer of his life out of a Redneck Blind and I could not be more proud of him. Check out his hunt on this weeks episode of Whitetail Edge called "Briar".

programme.title: Iowa
programme.desc: After Killing Evander, we felt really good about going back to Illinois and getting an opportunity at the buck we were after. The weather was right, it was late October, and it just seemed like everything was adding up for this to be a successful trip. Even though we saw the shooter we were after and another really good deer, after 4 days of hunting we decided to pack up again and try our luck in Iowa. For a hard core whitetail bow hunter chasing big deer its hard to beat sitting in a tree in Iowa at the end of October and early November. We couldn't have timed this up more perfect. The bucks were on their feet, we were seeing giant deer, and it was just a matter of time before we ran in to one in bow range. Sit back and enjoy the second episode of Whitetail Edge Season 4, "Iowa".

programme.title: Illinois
programme.desc: This has been the longest I have ever been away from home and I am tried and ready to see my family. We've been in Illinois 2 times prior to this and haven't had much luck at all. We've been to Kansas and killed and Iowa and killed and now we are heading back home to Ohio but we are making a pit stop in Illinois for one more try. Coming off a great hunt in Iowa where we killed a booner the day before we were not thinking much of this hunt but we knew the deer were moving, its early November, the rut is kicking it and anything can happen.
